comments.author: @DrAdityaSeth
comments.raw_text: I would like to present a different pov from my experience of the exam. It's understandable to feel disheartened, but please don't be. I went through a similar phase back in 2016. What I'd like to tell you all is that a difficult paper, while it might feel bad and disappointing initially, is actually better in the long run. It's preferable to a situation where 16 people score 720 on an easy exam. Think of it like a high-ceiling exam such as JEE Advanced, where someone scoring, for example, 380 out of 440 becomes the topper, and subsequent ranks are determined from there. Just keep your hopes up, everything will fall in place in time!
